data.name: Savory Spinach and Cheese Crepes
data.quickTastyDescription: Delicate crepes filled with creamy spinach and melted cheese, perfect for a light meal that’s both satisfying and easy to prepare.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, milk, eggs, salt, and pepper until smooth to make the crepe batter. Let it rest for about 10 minutes.

In a skillet over medium heat, melt a bit of butter and pour in about 1/4 cup of crepe batter, tilting the pan to spread it evenly. Cook for 1-2 minutes until the edges lift, then flip and cook for another minute. Repeat with the remaining batter.

In another pan, sauté the fresh spinach in a little butter until wilted. Remove from heat and mix in the cream cheese until melted and creamy. Stir in the nutmeg and shredded mozzarella cheese until well combined.
Place a few spoonfuls of the spinach and cheese mixture onto one half of a crepe, fold it over, and serve warm.
data.modifiersForBase: Filled with creamy spinach and cheese
